description: A figure resembling Santa Claus sits hunched over a typewriter in a dimly lit room, illuminated by a single lamp. The paper in the typewriter bears the title "NINE WAYS TO SERVE VENISON". This unexpected topic for the gift-giving figure creates a dark irony, contrasting his benevolent image with a potentially cannibalistic interest in the animal associated with his transportation, highlighting an absurd twist on the familiar holiday character.

other_text.location: on the paper in the typewriter
